---
/**
 * §2 "The problem" (CONTENT.md §2; DESIGN.md §12) — a calm editorial breather
 * between the hero and the orbital. Mostly type: tonal heading, a lead + two
 * supporting paragraphs in a ~620px column, and a mono pull-stat whose "0"
 * carries the single ember accent. One quiet §7 wash.
 */
import Eyebrow from './Eyebrow.astro';
---

<section id="problem" class="problem" aria-labelledby="problem-title">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="problem__head" data-reveal>
      <Eyebrow text="01 — The problem" />
      <h2 class="problem__title" id="problem-title">
        Canton has a token standard.
        <span class="problem__muted"
          >It doesn't have a best-execution layer — yet.</span
        >
      </h2>
    </header>

    <div class="problem__body" data-reveal>
      <p>
        Canton's token standard (CIP-0056 / 0112) gave the network a common
        settlement rail: any compliant asset can settle atomically via
        allocations. Liquidity is arriving — AMMs, order books, RFQ desks.
      </p>
      <p>
        But there's no neutral way to compare prices across venues, and no
        standard quote interface. CIP-0056 / 0112 standardize tokens, transfers,
        and <em>settlement</em> — not <em>quotes</em> or <em>routing</em>. A
        taker who hits one venue leaves price on the table.
      </p>
      <p>
        On every other chain the answer to fragmentation is the same: an
        aggregation / best-execution layer on top of the settlement rail. Canton
        doesn't have one yet.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="problem__stat mono" data-reveal>
      1 token standard <span class="problem__sep">·</span>
      <span class="problem__zero">0</span> best-execution layers
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .problem {
    position: relative;
    padding-block: var(--section-y);
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .problem::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    background: radial-gradient(
      40% 36% at 22% 4%,
      rgba(228, 232, 240, 0.06),
      transparent 60%
    );
  }
  .problem > .container {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .problem__head {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 18px;
    max-width: 720px;
  }
  .problem__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: clamp(30px, 4.4vw, 50px);
    line-height: 1.06;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  .problem__muted {
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }

  .problem__body {
    margin-top: 34px;
    max-width: 620px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 18px;
    font-size: 16.5px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink-2);
  }
  .problem__body em {
    font-style: normal;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .problem__stat {
    margin-top: 40px;
    font-size: 14px;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  .problem__sep {
    margin: 0 6px;
    color: var(--line-2);
  }
  .problem__zero {
    color: var(--ember);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
</style>
